    <main>
        <h2>Common Sports Injuries in High-Performance Athletes</h2>
        <p>High-performance athletes are prone to various types of sports injuries due to the intense physical demands of their training and competitions. Some of the most common sports injuries in high-performance athletes include:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Overuse injuries</li>
            <li>Concussions</li>
            <li>Heat injuries</li>
            <li>Traumatic injuries</li>
        </ul>
        <h2>Prevention Tips for High-Performance Athletes</h2>
        <p>To prevent sports injuries, high-performance athletes should:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Warm up properly before training and competitions</li>
            <li>Use proper equipment and protective gear</li>
            <li>Stay hydrated and avoid overexertion</li>
            <li>Follow a safe and balanced training program</li>
            <li>Get enough rest and recovery time</li>
        </ul>
    </main>
